Panicles were sampled 6 to 7 d after flowering. We collected 3 normal panicles from each plant in the secondary F2 population in Hainan and the F2:3 population in Zhejiang, and 5 panicles from each parent and the NIL (qSE7XB). After the lower side spikelets of the panicle flowered, the stigma exsertion rate was observed. The percentage of exserted stigma was calculated by the method proposed by Miyata et al. with minor modifications39. We measured three traits for percentage of stigma exsertion rate: single stigma exsertion (SSE), dual stigma exsertion (DSE), and total stigma exsertion (TSE). The counts of stigma exsertion were converted by using the following formulae:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
